$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(9, 161, '<strong>This year we are bringing together our love of music to tell you a story. This story, although grand and beautiful, is not often told. It is vast in its telling and shows humanities depths through various musical aspects. We are delighted to be sharing with you the hope, joy, and celebration of music with the 2016-2017 music season. </strong><br /><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\"><u>Concert Season</u></span><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\"> </span><br /><br /><em><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">“From the Composer&#39;s Pen”</span><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\"> </span></em><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Featuring the Nixa High School Chamber Choir </span><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Sunday, October 30th, 3:00 p.m. </span><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Schweitzer United Methodist Church </span><br /><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Carol of the Angels</span><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\"> </span><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Featuring the music of Vivaldi, Saint-Saens, Britten and Rutter </span><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Tuesday, December 6th, 7:30 p.m. </span><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">All Saints Anglican Church </span><br /><br /><em><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">The Rest of the Story</span><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\"> </span></em><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Lesser Known Works of the Great Composers </span><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Sunday, February 26th, 3:00 p.m. </span><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Barnett Recital Hall on the campus of Evangel University </span><br /><br /><em><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">The Story Never Ends</span><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\"> </span></em><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Sunday, April 30th, 3:00 p.m. </span><br /><span style=\\\"box-sizing:border-box;line-height:1.3em;\\\">Redeemer Lutheran Church</span>', 'This year we are bringing together our love of music to tell you a story. This story, although grand and beautiful, is not often told. It is vast in its telling and shows humanities depths through various musical aspects. We are delighted to be sharing with you the hope, joy, and celebration of music with the 2016-2017 music season. Concert Season “From the Composer&#039;s Pen” Featuring the Nixa High School Chamber Choir Sunday, October 30th, 3:00 p.m. Schweitzer United Methodist Church Carol of the Angels Featuring the music of Vivaldi, Saint-Saens, Britten and Rutter Tuesday, December 6th, 7:30 p.m. All Saints Anglican Church The Rest of the Story Lesser Known Works of the Great Composers Sunday, February 26th, 3:00 p.m. Barnett Recital Hall on the campus of Evangel University The Story Never Ends Sunday, April 30th, 3:00 p.m. Redeemer Lutheran Church');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(10, 159, ':facebook-banner.png', 'facebook-banner.png');";
$k_stmts[] = $k_stmt_pre."(10, 161, 'We will be exploring some of the lesser known works and see what the famous Composer&rsquo;s created outwith. Our first concert will be held on Sunday, October 30th at Schweitzer United Methodist Church starting at 3:00 pm. Featured will be our guest, <em>The Nixa High School Chamber Choir</em>.\\r\\n', 'We will be exploring some of the lesser known works and see what the famous Composer’s created outwith. Our first concert will be held on Sunday, October 30th at Schweitzer United Methodist Church starting at 3:00 pm. Featured will be our guest, The Nixa High School Chamber Choir.');";
